{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01SMpek4bkxYn8Y9U5ymTnbo","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01UampfWofBtPMhYTxvY5swb","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/tmp/plan.md","content":"# spark-pi Namespace — Migration / Upgrade Plan\n\n> Status: **DRAFT for review.** No changes have been applied. This document\n> describes the *current* state and the *proposed* sequence of changes for the\n> next maintenance window. Do not execute until approved.\n\n## 1. Current configuration (as inspected 2026-06-18)\n\n### Deployments\n| Object | Image | Replicas | CPU (req/lim) | Mem (req/lim) | SA |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| `spark-master` | `apache/spark:3.5.3` | 1 | 200m / 500m | 512Mi / 1Gi | `spark-pi` |\n| `spark-worker` | `apache/spark:3.5.3` | 1 | 200m / 500m | 512Mi / 1Gi | `spark-pi` |\n\n- `spark-master` command unsets `SPARK_MASTER_PORT`, runs `start-master.sh`, tails logs. Ports 7077 (spark), 8080 (webui).\n- `spark-worker` connects to `spark://spark-master:7077`. Env: `SPARK_WORKER_MEMORY=1G`, `SPARK_WORKER_CORES=1`. Port 8081.\n- Both `imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent`, RollingUpdate (25%/25%).\n\n### Job\n| Object | Image | SA | CPU (req/lim) | Mem (req/lim) | backoffLimit |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| `spark-pi` | `apache/spark:3.5.3-nonexistent` | `spark-nonexistent` | 200m / 500m | `512` (no unit) / 1Gi | 0 |\n\n- Driver: `spark-submit --master local[2] --driver-memory 512m --class org.apache.spark.examples.SparkPi spark-examples_2.12-3.5.3.jar 1000`.\n- `restartPolicy: Never`, `completions: 1`, `parallelism: 1`.\n\n### RBAC\n- ServiceAccount `spark-pi` (used by both deployments). ServiceAccount `default`.\n- Role `spark-pi-role`: on `\"\"` core group — `services`, `configmaps`, `persistentvolumeclaims` with verbs create/get/list/watch/delete/update/patch.\n- RoleBinding `spark-pi-role-binding`: binds `spark-pi-role` → SA `spark-pi`.\n\n### ConfigMaps / status\n- Only `kube-root-ca.crt` (auto). No application ConfigMap present.\n- Pods: master & worker Running 1/1. Job pod NOT progressing (see findings).\n\n## 2. Findings — drift from a healthy baseline\n\nThe following deviations were observed and drive the plan below:\n\n- **F1 (blocking): Job image tag `3.5.3-nonexistent` is invalid** → the job pod\n  will `ImagePullBackOff` and never complete. Job shows `0/1` completions.\n- **F2 (blocking): Job `serviceAccountName: spark-nonexistent` does not exist**\n  → pod admission/mount issues; SA is undefined in the namespace.\n- **F3 (correctness): Job memory request `\"512\"` has no unit** → interpreted as\n  512 **bytes**, not 512Mi. Inconsistent with the limit `1Gi` and with the\n  deployments' `512Mi`.\n- **F4 (version): All workloads pin `apache/spark:3.5.3`** and the examples JAR\n  is `spark-examples_2.12-3.5.3.jar` — the maintenance target is a newer Spark\n  patch/minor release; image tag and JAR version must move together.\n- **F5 (capacity): Resource limits are modest** (500m / 1Gi). Confirm headroom\n  for the upgraded image before/after the version bump.\n\n## 3. Proposed change sequence (execute in order, one step at a time)\n\n> Roll out **non-prod first**, verify each step, then proceed. Keep the old\n> ReplicaSet for rollback (revisionHistoryLimit is 10).\n\n### Step 1 — Fix the Job service account (F2)\n- Either create the referenced SA, or repoint the Job to the existing `spark-pi` SA.\n  Recommended: set `serviceAccountName: spark-pi` to reuse the bound RBAC.\n- **Verify:** `kubectl -n spark-pi get sa spark-pi` exists; Job spec references it.\n\n### Step 2 — Fix the Job image tag (F1)\n- Set the Job image to a valid, pullable tag (initially the current line\n  `apache/spark:3.5.3`, then the upgrade target in Step 5).\n- **Verify:** delete & recreate the immutable Job; `kubectl -n spark-pi get job spark-pi`\n  reaches `1/1` completions; pod logs show `Pi is roughly 3.14...`. No `ImagePullBackOff`.\n\n### Step 3 — Fix the Job memory request unit (F3)\n- Change `requests.memory: \"512\"` → `512Mi` to match the limit and deployments.\n- **Verify:** `kubectl -n spark-pi get job spark-pi -o jsonpath='{..requests.memory}'`\n  returns `512Mi`; pod schedules and is not OOM/eviction-flagged.\n\n### Step 4 — Right-size resources if needed (F5)\n- Review master/worker/job CPU & memory against observed usage\n  (`kubectl top pods -n spark-pi`). Adjust requests/limits only if headroom is short.\n- **Verify:** pods stay Running, no OOMKilled, no CPU throttling regressions.\n\n### Step 5 — Upgrade the Spark image version (F4)\n- Bump master, worker, and job images to the approved target tag together, and\n  update the examples JAR version in the Job command to match.\n- Roll deployments first (RollingUpdate handles master then worker), then\n  recreate the Job.\n- **Verify:** master webui (:8080) shows the worker registered; worker logs show\n  successful registration to `spark://spark-master:7077`; SparkPi job completes\n  `1/1` with the expected Pi output on the new version.\n\n### Step 6 — Review RBAC scope (optional hardening)\n- Confirm the Role's verb set (incl. `delete`/`patch` on services/configmaps/PVCs)\n  is still required. Tighten to least privilege if not.\n- **Verify:** `kubectl auth can-i ...` checks for `spark-pi` SA match the intended policy.\n\n## 4. Rollback\n- Deployments: `kubectl -n spark-pi rollout undo deploy/spark-master`\n  (and `spark-worker`) returns to the prior ReplicaSet/image.\n- Job: re-apply the previous Job manifest (Jobs are immutable; delete + recreate).\n- RBAC: re-apply the previous Role/RoleBinding manifests.\n\n## 5. Post-change validation checklist\n- [ ] `kubectl -n spark-pi get deploy,job,pods` all healthy/complete.\n- [ ] Worker registered with master (master webui / worker logs).\n- [ ] SparkPi job `1/1` completed with correct output on target version.\n- [ ] No `ImagePullBackOff`, no OOMKilled, no `spark-nonexistent` references remain.\n- [ ] RBAC bindings unchanged or tightened as approved.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":862,"cache_read_input_tokens":33748,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":862},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"13ca45c5-767b-48aa-ba35-17a21d1264e3","uuid":"901e93b1-c1d1-4827-8973-1c256eb724a3","request_id":"req_011CcAZYxiScta8mpLRD5ex4"}
