re group — `services`, `configmaps`, `persistentvolumeclaims` with verbs create/get/list/watch/delete/update/patch.\n- RoleBinding `spark-pi-role-binding`: binds `spark-pi-role` → SA `spark-pi`.\n\n### ConfigMaps / status\n- Only `kube-root-ca.crt` (auto). No application ConfigMap present.\n- Pods: master & worker Running 1/1. Job pod NOT progressing (see findings).\n\n## 2. Findings — drift from a healthy baseline\n\nThe following deviations were observed and drive the plan below:\n\n- **F1 (blocking): Job image tag `3.5.3-nonexistent` is invalid** → the job pod\n  will `ImagePullBackOff` and never complete. Job shows `0/1` completions.\n- **F2 (blocking): Job `serviceAccountName: spark-nonexistent` does not exist**\n  → the SA is undefined in the namespace; the pod cannot mount its token.\n- **F3 (correctness): Job memory request `\"512\"` has no unit** → interpreted as\n  512 **bytes**, not 512Mi. Inconsistent with the limit `1Gi` and with the\n  deployments' `512Mi`.\n- **F4 (version): All workloads pin `apache/spark:3.5.3`** and the examples JAR\n  is `spark-examples_2.12-3.5.3.jar` — the maintenance target is a newer Spark\n  patch/minor release; image tag and JAR version must move together.\n- **F5 (capacity): Resource limits are modest** (500m / 1Gi). Confirm headroom\n  for the upgraded image before/after the version bump.\n\n## 3. Proposed change sequence (execute in order, one step at a time)\n\n> Roll out **non-prod first**, verify each step, then proceed. Keep the old\n> ReplicaSet for rollback (revisionHistoryLimit is 10).\n\n### Step 1 — Fix the Job service account (F2)\n- Either create the referenced SA, or repoint the Job to the existing `spark-pi` SA.\n  Recommended: set `serviceAccountName: spark-pi` to reuse the bound RBAC.\n- **Verify:** `kubectl -n spark-pi get sa spark-pi` exists; Job spec references it.\n\n### Step 2 — Fix the Job image tag (F1)\n- Set the Job image to a valid, pullable tag (initially the current line\n  `apache/spark:3.5.3`,